sec.p:
Phenotypic identification of VW resistance was separately carried out at 15 and 30 DAI, and each seedling was evaluated according to a severity rating system (from 0 to 4) based on the disease symptoms of the plant leaves [83]. Specifically, 0 indicates healthy plant without disease symptom; 1 indicates less than 25% leaves with disease symptoms; 2 indicates 25–50% leaves with disease symptoms; 3 indicates 50–75% leaves with disease symptoms; and 4 indicates over 75% leaves with disease symptoms and even completely defoliated or dead plants. The DI was adopted to calculate the VW resistance using the following formula:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \mathrm{DI}=\left[\sum \left(\mathrm{N}\mathrm{i}\times \mathrm{i}\right)/\left(\mathrm{N}\times 4\right)\right]\times 100 $$\end{document}DI=∑Ni×i/N×4×100where i is the disease grade from 0 to 4, Ni is the number of plants with the corresponding disease grade, and N is the number of total plants investigated for each material.
